WEBVTT

00:08.050 --> 00:09.685
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:09.719 --> 00:10.820
I WANT WEED.

00:10.853 --> 00:13.556
I HEAR YOU GET GREAT SHIT
FROM AFGHANISTAN.

00:15.558 --> 00:17.894
OH, YOU'RE THE ASSHOLES
WHO JACKED THE POT.

00:17.927 --> 00:19.629
DO HER.
DON'T DO HER.

00:19.662 --> 00:20.730
OH, YEAH.

00:20.763 --> 00:23.166
WE CELEBRATE THE CLOSING
OF ESCROW ON THIS,

00:23.199 --> 00:26.602
THE BOTWIN‐PRICE‐GRAY
FAMILY COMPOUND.

00:26.636 --> 00:27.837
[ GUNSHOT ]

00:27.870 --> 00:29.372
I'M IN THE POLICE ACADEMY.

00:29.405 --> 00:30.973
WE'RE CRIMINALS.
IT'S THE FAMILY BUSINESS.

00:31.007 --> 00:32.241
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING?

00:32.275 --> 00:33.509
I THINK
I WANT TO BE A COP.

00:33.543 --> 00:35.144
BUT YOU'RE NOT
OFF THE RAILS.

00:35.178 --> 00:36.412
YOU'RE HERE,
AND I'M HERE,

00:36.446 --> 00:38.281
AND WE'RE BOTH
IN THE "DEAD DADDY" CLUB.

00:38.314 --> 00:39.682
KINDRED SPIRITS.

00:39.715 --> 00:42.819
WHEN IS YOUR MOTHER COMING BACK?
I NEED HER HELP.

00:42.852 --> 00:45.021
I'M ABOUT TO RUN OUT OF SUPPLY,
AND I CAN'T ‐‐

00:45.054 --> 00:46.222
[ GASPS ]

00:46.255 --> 00:48.224
[ MOANING ]

00:48.257 --> 00:49.625
[ GASPS ]

00:49.659 --> 00:53.095
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE.
IT'S BULLSHIT!

00:53.129 --> 00:56.432
ARE YOU [CHUCKLES]
ON ROLLER SKATES?

00:56.466 --> 00:59.368
YEAH. I'M, UH,
COACHING THE TWINS' DERBY TEAM.

00:59.402 --> 01:01.504
ANDY AND I ARE AT THE ROOM
AT THE TOP OF THE STAIRS.

01:01.537 --> 01:03.773
IN THE SAME ROOM TOGETHER ‐‐
THE TWO OF US.

01:03.806 --> 01:05.308
DO YOU HEAR ME?

01:05.341 --> 01:08.878
OH, SHIT.
I THINK THE BULLET'S MOVING.

01:18.554 --> 01:21.524
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:21.557 --> 01:23.993
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
MADE OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:24.026 --> 01:26.262
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:26.295 --> 01:28.264
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:28.297 --> 01:30.800
♪♪ THERE'S A GREEN ONE
AND A PINK ONE ♪♪

01:30.833 --> 01:33.269
♪♪ AND A BLUE ONE
AND A YELLOW ONE ♪♪

01:33.302 --> 01:35.538
♪♪ THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:35.571 --> 01:39.609
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

01:39.642 --> 01:42.512
[ HOOTING ]

01:42.545 --> 01:45.114
♪♪ AND THE PEOPLE IN THE HOUSES ♪♪

01:45.148 --> 01:47.183
♪♪ ALL WENT TO THE UNIVERSITY ♪♪

01:47.216 --> 01:52.121
♪♪ WHERE THEY WERE PUT IN BOXES,
AND THEY CAME OUT ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:52.155 --> 01:54.524
♪♪ THERE WERE DOCTORS
AND LAWYERS ♪♪

01:54.557 --> 01:56.793
♪♪ AND BUSINESS EXECUTIVES ♪♪

01:56.826 --> 01:59.262
♪♪ THEY'RE ALL MADE OUT
OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:59.295 --> 02:03.366
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK
JUST THE SAME ♪♪

02:25.922 --> 02:27.924
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

02:35.398 --> 02:37.867
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]
[ GASPS ]

02:37.900 --> 02:40.570
IS SOMEONE OUT THERE?

02:40.603 --> 02:43.372
HELLO?

02:58.588 --> 03:00.323
[ SIGHS ]

03:04.327 --> 03:06.529
[ INSECTS CHIRPING ]

03:21.844 --> 03:24.313
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

03:27.917 --> 03:29.919
[ RUSTLING ]

03:35.858 --> 03:38.561
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

03:38.594 --> 03:40.463
[ GRUNTS ]

03:49.472 --> 03:51.641
♪♪ OOH, OOH‐OOH ♪♪

03:51.674 --> 03:53.643
[ LAUGHTER ]

03:53.782 --> 03:56.084
I GET IT. DUCK.
HEY, KIDDO.

03:56.118 --> 03:57.786
I LIKE THESE PICTURES
YOU DREW.

03:57.819 --> 04:00.756
NAKED MOLE RAT?
HE'S OBSESSED.

04:00.789 --> 04:02.724
OH, YEAH.
WHAT IS A NAKED MOLE RAT?

04:02.758 --> 04:05.127
IT'S LIKE A HAIRLESS RODENT.
IT LOOKS LIKE AN AL‐‐

04:05.160 --> 04:07.396
OH, COULD YOU PLEASE
LET HIM ANSWER?

04:07.429 --> 04:11.266
NOW, WHO WANTS BREAKFAST TACOS,
MYSTERY MAN?

04:11.300 --> 04:13.135
TINY FEET?

04:13.168 --> 04:14.536
HOW ABOUT TODAY...

04:14.570 --> 04:19.274
YOU AND I GO AND SEE
A REAL NAKED...

04:19.308 --> 04:21.276
MOUSE THING?

04:21.310 --> 04:22.811
YOU'RE TAKING HIM
TO THE ZOO?

04:22.844 --> 04:24.947
YOU KNOW,
IT'S SUCH A NICE DAY OUT.

04:24.980 --> 04:28.317
OH, NANCE, HE'S A RUNNER.
YOU CAN'T KEEP UP.

04:28.350 --> 04:29.618
SURE, I CAN.

04:31.286 --> 04:33.522
YOU COULD RENT
A MOTORIZED WHEELCHAIR.

04:33.555 --> 04:34.990
LENNY USED TO DO IT
AT DISNEYLAND

04:35.023 --> 04:36.358
SO HE COULD CUT THE LINES.

04:36.391 --> 04:37.526
WHAT IF HE FALLS
AND CRACKS HIS HEAD OPEN?

04:37.559 --> 04:39.061
I'LL TAKE HIM
TO THE HOSPITAL.

04:39.094 --> 04:41.396
IT'S AMAZING WHAT THEY CAN DO
FOR HEAD INJURIES THESE DAYS.

04:41.430 --> 04:43.865
I SLEPT 18 HOURS
LAST NIGHT.

04:43.899 --> 04:44.833
VERY JEALOUS.

04:44.866 --> 04:47.536
OH, YEAH?
YOU GOT INSOMNIA, NANCE?

04:47.569 --> 04:48.971
[ PILLS RATTLE ]
AMBIEN.

04:49.004 --> 04:52.007
GIVES YOU FREAKY DREAMS,
BUT YOU'LL SLEEP LIKE A BABY.

04:52.040 --> 04:53.375
HOW ABOUT THIS?
WE ALL GO.

04:53.408 --> 04:55.377
NO, I NEED SOME ALONE TIME
WITH HIM.

04:55.410 --> 04:58.080
AND I'VE BEEN DOING EXERCISES.
I CAN HANDLE IT.

04:58.113 --> 04:59.615
EXERCISES?

04:59.648 --> 05:01.383
I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU EXERCISE
SINCE YOU'VE BEEN BACK.

05:01.416 --> 05:02.751
MM‐HMM.

05:02.784 --> 05:05.621
I STRETCH
THE STRETCHY THING...

05:05.654 --> 05:08.624
SQUEEZE THE BALL.
I'M TAKING HIM.

05:14.029 --> 05:15.831
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT'S NEXT?

05:15.864 --> 05:19.401
ARE YOU GONNA FRISK THE SINK,
ARREST THE TOILET?

05:19.434 --> 05:22.537
NAH, MAYBE I'LL JUST
BUST UP THE GROW HOUSE.

05:22.571 --> 05:25.140
US BOTH LIVING HERE.
IT'S NUTS, RIGHT?

05:25.173 --> 05:27.342
I'M NOT ACTUALLY
GONNA BUST YOU.

05:27.376 --> 05:29.444
NO, BUT YOU COULD.
NOT REALLY.

05:29.478 --> 05:32.147
I CAN'T EVEN WRITE
PARKING TICKETS YET.

05:32.180 --> 05:35.784
YEAH, WELL, ONE DAY.
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

05:35.817 --> 05:37.519
ONE DAY
MARIJUANA WILL BE LEGAL,

05:37.553 --> 05:39.388
AND YOU AND MOM CAN BUY A KIOSK
AT THE DANBURY MALL.

05:39.421 --> 05:41.657
UNTIL THEN, I'D HANG HEAVIER
DRAPES IN THE GROW HOUSE

05:41.690 --> 05:43.959
OR A BLACK SHOWER CURTAIN.

05:43.992 --> 05:46.361
THANKS FOR THE ADVICE...

05:46.395 --> 05:47.629
COPPER.

05:47.663 --> 05:50.899
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO PROB, PERP.

05:52.367 --> 05:55.103
[ SIGHS ]

05:58.173 --> 05:59.908
[ GASPS ]

06:02.978 --> 06:03.979
[ SIGHS ]

06:07.382 --> 06:08.850
HEY! HEY!

06:08.884 --> 06:12.221
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
THIS IS MY PAPER.

06:12.254 --> 06:13.722
IT WAS YOUR PAPER.

06:13.755 --> 06:15.624
BUT YOU FORFEITED THAT RIGHT
WHEN YOUR GIANT HORSE‐DOG

06:15.657 --> 06:17.392
PLAY‐DOH'D ALL OVER
MY FRONT PORCH.

06:17.426 --> 06:19.394
MY DOG DOES NOT SHIT
ON BRICK.

06:19.428 --> 06:23.265
SHE'S A GRASS SHITTER,
SOMETIMES WOOD CHIPS.

06:23.298 --> 06:25.334
WADE, DEAR,
YOU FORGOT TO TAKE YOUR LEXAPRO.

06:25.367 --> 06:28.337
LATER, MOTHER.
I'M BUSY!

06:28.370 --> 06:30.205
YOU STILL LIVE
WITH YOUR MOTHER?

06:30.239 --> 06:31.807
JUST GET
OFF OUR PROPERTY.

06:31.840 --> 06:33.475
LIKE THIS CHILD?

06:33.508 --> 06:35.344
WHERE'S SHE GOING, HUH?
SHE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

06:35.377 --> 06:38.113
SHE'S LIKE YOU.
[ SQUISHING ]

06:38.146 --> 06:40.415
OH, GREAT!

06:40.449 --> 06:43.452
AH, KISMET.

06:44.887 --> 06:46.121
SHIT FOOT.

06:46.154 --> 06:48.457
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

06:54.496 --> 06:56.865
I'M LOOKING UP DIRECTIONS
TO THE ZOO.

06:56.899 --> 07:00.135
WE STILL NEED TO TALK ABOUT
THE POLICE ACADEMY.

07:00.168 --> 07:02.537
I STAND BY MY LOVE
OF STEVE GUTTENBERG.

07:02.571 --> 07:04.406
IT'S A VERY DANGEROUS
PROFESSION.

07:04.439 --> 07:06.275
ON ANY GIVEN DAY,
YOU CAN BE SHOT.

07:06.308 --> 07:08.410
I'VE ALREADY BEEN SHOT.
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

07:08.443 --> 07:11.713
PERSONALLY, I THOUGHT PUPPETEER
WAS A GOOD FIT FOR YOU.

07:11.747 --> 07:15.384
BUT MAYBE THAT'S THE KIND OF JOB
YOU CAN ONLY DO IN EUROPE.

07:15.417 --> 07:16.618
DID HE TELL YOU?

07:16.652 --> 07:18.253
HE'S FLEXING IN FRONT
OF A MIRROR

07:18.287 --> 07:20.222
WITH ONE OF THOSE
COP STICK THINGS.

07:20.255 --> 07:22.124
BILLY CLUB? TRUNCHEON?

07:22.157 --> 07:25.093
WE'LL TALK ABOUT THIS
WHEN I GET BACK.

07:25.127 --> 07:27.262
STEVIE, COME ON!
LET'S GO!

07:27.296 --> 07:29.131
[ CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS ]

07:29.164 --> 07:31.533
I CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

07:31.567 --> 07:33.902
I'M NOT CALLING FOR YOU.
I'M CALLING FOR YOUR MOTHER.

07:36.104 --> 07:38.574
IT'S KIKU.

07:38.607 --> 07:40.509
HELLO?

07:40.542 --> 07:41.543
KIKU: Question.

07:41.577 --> 07:43.345
ARE YOU RECOVERED YET?

07:43.378 --> 07:46.348
I...CAN CHEW
WITH MY MOUTH CLOSED.

07:46.381 --> 07:47.883
DO SUDOKU.

07:47.916 --> 07:51.386
Great. I think I might be in
kind of, um, like, a situation?

07:51.420 --> 07:54.189
MY FRIEND INDIA
WHO'S A MODEL FROM SRI LANKA

07:54.223 --> 07:56.258
GAVE ME THE NAME
OF THIS DEALER

07:56.291 --> 07:58.860
NAMED JERSEY
WHO LIVES IN STATEN ISLAND.

07:58.894 --> 08:00.495
SO I'M AT HIS PLACE,

08:00.529 --> 08:02.831
AND THIS IS REALLY NOT A HEALTHY
BUSINESS ENVIRONMENT.

08:02.864 --> 08:04.499
[ DART THUDS ]

08:04.533 --> 08:07.736
ARE YOU BUYING OR WHAT?

08:08.870 --> 08:10.272
CAN YOU COME HERE?

08:10.305 --> 08:11.873
I'M HANGING OUT
WITH MY KID TODAY.

08:11.907 --> 08:13.408
[ SIGHS ]

08:13.442 --> 08:15.544
IS BUBBLE HASH LIKE A MORE
EXPENSIVE VERSION OF WEED?

08:15.577 --> 08:19.348
OH, DO NOT BUY
BUBBLE HASH.

08:19.381 --> 08:20.682
WAIT.
YOU'RE CUTTING OUT.

08:20.716 --> 08:22.985
DID YOU SAY
BUY THE BUBBLE HASH?
NO!

08:23.018 --> 08:26.622
FUCKING STATEN ISLAND!

08:26.655 --> 08:28.957
[ Crackling ]
Look, I've sent you a car.
NO!

08:28.991 --> 08:30.092
[ Crackling ]

08:30.125 --> 08:32.594
KIKU, HELLO?

08:35.030 --> 08:37.399
OH, MY GOD.

08:42.070 --> 08:47.276
SO, WE HAVE TO TAKE A TINY
DETOUR THROUGH STATEN ISLAND,

08:47.309 --> 08:51.146
WHICH PROBABLY HAS TONS
OF ODD...

08:51.179 --> 08:53.715
PATCHY‐HAIRED RODENTS.

08:57.319 --> 08:59.888
RIGHT.
DUMB IDEA.

08:59.922 --> 09:01.990
OLD‐ME IDEA.

09:02.024 --> 09:04.192
UM, JILL, CAN YOU...?

09:04.226 --> 09:07.362
YES. OF COURSE I CAN.
I'D LOVE TO.

09:07.396 --> 09:10.632
OHH, I LOVE THE ZOO.

09:10.666 --> 09:12.401
I LOVE SPENDING TIME
WITH YOU.

09:12.434 --> 09:13.936
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
SO MUCH FUN.

09:13.969 --> 09:16.672
IT'S GONNA BE THE BEST DAY EVER.
RAWR, RAWR!

09:16.705 --> 09:20.509
UH, I HAVE TO HELP
A FRIEND,

09:20.542 --> 09:23.545
BUT HOW ABOUT TONIGHT
WE HAVE A SPECIAL DINNER

09:23.579 --> 09:25.781
AND YOU CAN SIT
NEXT TO ME?

09:25.814 --> 09:27.115
HOW DOES THAT SOUND?

09:27.149 --> 09:28.517
OKAY?

09:28.550 --> 09:32.988
ANDY, CAN YOU COOK, UH...
THE...

09:33.021 --> 09:36.725
THE THING WITH THE ‐‐

09:36.758 --> 09:39.061
THE SQUID
AND THE SPICES?

09:39.094 --> 09:40.629
I CAN'T...

09:40.662 --> 09:42.564
UH...
UH, NO, I CAN'T.

09:42.598 --> 09:45.133
I HAVE DERBY PRACTICE
TONIGHT.

09:45.167 --> 09:46.935
OH, FINE.

09:46.969 --> 09:49.638
WELL, WE'LL ORDER IN.

10:09.164 --> 10:12.267
UM, I'M WEARING
A SPORTS BRA.

10:12.301 --> 10:13.702
O‐OKAY...

10:13.735 --> 10:16.371
I JUST THOUGHT
I SHOULD WARN YOU.

10:16.405 --> 10:19.574
THERE'S NO HOOK.
SOME GUYS GET CONFUSED.

10:19.608 --> 10:23.278
ALSO, IN COLLEGE,
I THOUGHT MAYBE I WAS ASEXUAL.

10:23.312 --> 10:27.049
BUT IT TURNS OUT
I JUST SUCK AT INTIMACY.

10:27.082 --> 10:28.750
I THINK IT'S
A GENERATIONAL ‐‐

10:33.922 --> 10:34.923
[ MOANS ]

10:34.957 --> 10:37.793
UM, UM, DO YOU HAVE
PLANS TONIGHT?

10:37.826 --> 10:40.062
ARE YOU ASKING ME OUT
WHILE YOUR HAND IS ON MY BOOB?

10:40.095 --> 10:42.564
ONLY TO DINNER, IF YOU WANT,
AT MY MOM'S HOUSE.

10:42.598 --> 10:43.966
YOU WANT ME
TO MEET YOUR MOM?

10:43.999 --> 10:46.168
SHE'S PRETTY COOL, ACTUALLY.
YOU'RE A LOT ALIKE.

10:46.201 --> 10:47.436
SHE'S REALLY INTENSE.

10:47.469 --> 10:51.974
THAT'S A PERVERSELY SWEET
THING TO SAY.

10:53.275 --> 10:55.310
YEAH, I'LL COME TONIGHT.

10:55.344 --> 10:56.878
COOL.

10:56.912 --> 10:58.180
COOL.

10:59.348 --> 11:01.149
[ SIGHS ]

11:01.183 --> 11:03.819
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

11:04.987 --> 11:08.523
[ CHIMES JINGLE,
MID‐TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

11:11.059 --> 11:12.294
HI.

11:12.327 --> 11:13.829
UH, HAD A FEW QUESTIONS.

11:13.862 --> 11:15.097
[ SPITS ]

11:15.130 --> 11:16.932
YEAH, SHOOT.

11:18.367 --> 11:21.103
THIS INDOOR WEED STRAIN
I'M WORKING ON ‐‐

11:21.136 --> 11:23.305
IT'S REALLY STRONG,
BUT IT HAS A KIND OF LOW YIELD.

11:23.338 --> 11:25.307
DO YOU HAVE ANY
NUTRIENT SOLUTIONS

11:25.340 --> 11:27.242
THAT MIGHT HELP
FORCE MORE BUDS?

11:27.276 --> 11:28.543
[ SPITS ]

11:28.577 --> 11:30.846
WE SELL, QUOTE,
"GARDENING SUPPLIES."

11:30.879 --> 11:32.781
YOU'RE A HYDROPONIC
SUPPLY STORE.

11:32.814 --> 11:35.384
DOES NEW JERSEY HAVE
A DIFFERENT DEFINITION ‐‐

11:35.417 --> 11:37.719
I THINK WHAT MY FRIEND HERE
IS TRYING TO SAY

11:37.753 --> 11:39.688
IS THAT HE'S REDUCING
HIS FOOD BILL THIS MONTH

11:39.721 --> 11:41.790
BY GROWING CHERRY TOMATOES

11:41.823 --> 11:44.860
IN A SAFE AND TOTALLY NON‐PROFIT
HOME ENVIRONMENT.

11:44.893 --> 11:45.961
YES, HE IS OVER 21,

11:45.994 --> 11:48.630
AND, NO, HE DOESN'T HAVE
A CRIMINAL RECORD.

11:48.664 --> 11:50.265
DO YOU?

11:50.299 --> 11:52.935
[ SPITS ]

11:57.005 --> 11:59.241
CONNOISSEUR COMBO PACK.

11:59.274 --> 12:02.678
THANKS, MIKE.
I'LL RING HIM UP.

12:02.711 --> 12:04.546
YOU WORK HERE?
PART‐TIME.

12:04.579 --> 12:06.515
LET ME GUESS.
WEST COAST?

12:06.548 --> 12:09.818
OH, WELL, I LIVE IN CONNECTICUT,
BUT I'M FROM CALIFORNIA.

12:09.851 --> 12:12.587
FUCKING LOVE CALI!
NOT THAT I'VE BEEN.

12:12.621 --> 12:14.556
BUT I'VE READ EVERYTHING
BY DIDION.

12:14.589 --> 12:16.291
I WENT THROUGH A PHASE
WHERE I WAS OBSESSED WITH
1960s SURFING MOVIES.

12:16.325 --> 12:18.026
WAY MORE LAX
THAN EAST COAST.

12:18.060 --> 12:19.127
DO YOU PLAY PING‐PONG?

12:19.161 --> 12:22.097
WAIT, DON'T ANSWER THAT.
R. J.

12:22.130 --> 12:25.067
SILAS.

12:27.469 --> 12:31.273
[ DOG BARKING, SIREN WAILS ]

12:31.306 --> 12:34.309
KIKU'S GONNA LEAVE NOW,
OKAY?

12:34.343 --> 12:36.078
NAH. SHE PROMISED TO BUY
SOME OF MY PRODUCT.

12:36.111 --> 12:38.046
I DID NOT PROMI‐‐
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
FUCK! YOU DID!

12:38.080 --> 12:41.850
YOUR PRODUCT IS NOT WHAT
SHE'S SUPPOSED TO BE SELLING.

12:41.883 --> 12:45.087
WE'RE NOT HASH PEOPLE.
IT'S A TASTE THING.

12:45.120 --> 12:47.489
IT'S DIFFERENT SPICES...
OF LIFE.

12:47.522 --> 12:48.757
I HAVE TO SIT.

12:48.790 --> 12:49.758
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:49.791 --> 12:51.159
WHY DIDN'T YOU
JUST CALL DEMETRI?

12:51.193 --> 12:52.761
HE REFUSED TO SELL TO ME.

12:52.794 --> 12:55.464
I'M MISSING A DAY
WITH MY KID, OKAY?

12:55.497 --> 13:00.435
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
THAT I'M JUST GONNA LET
Y'ALL WALK OUT OF HERE?

13:00.469 --> 13:03.572
I'M TIRED,
HAD A HARD FEW MONTHS,

13:03.605 --> 13:05.607
EATEN A LOT OF JELL‐O,

13:05.641 --> 13:10.145
DISCOVERING ‐‐ DON'T WANT
TO BE DOING THIS ANYMORE.

13:10.178 --> 13:11.580
WHOLE REASON I HIRED YOU.

13:11.613 --> 13:15.851
I'M REALLY GRATEFUL
YOU'RE GONNA LET US GO,

13:15.884 --> 13:19.554
SO I'D LIKE
TO OFFER YOU THESE ‐‐

13:19.588 --> 13:21.290
PRESCRIPTION PAIN‐KILLERS.

13:21.323 --> 13:22.658
THERE'S A FEW LEFT.

13:22.691 --> 13:25.260
I DON'T WANT PILLS.
THAT SHIT'S ADDICTIVE.

13:25.294 --> 13:28.163
WELL, WHAT DO YOU WANT?

13:28.196 --> 13:30.899
WHAT YOU THINK
OF HER CANE?

13:30.933 --> 13:33.235
UH...

13:33.268 --> 13:35.871
IT'S SIMPLE...

13:35.904 --> 13:37.439
BUT FESTIVE.

13:37.472 --> 13:39.141
[ CHUCKLES WEAKLY ]

13:43.812 --> 13:45.714
[ ALARM BLARES ]

13:45.747 --> 13:47.182
Woman:
<i>GET READY TO START.</i>

13:47.215 --> 13:50.452
HE WROTE
"YELLOW TEAM BASE."

13:50.485 --> 13:53.288
WHAT'S BASE?

13:53.322 --> 13:55.791
THAT LOOKS LIKE A VOLCANO.

13:55.824 --> 13:58.293
I DON'T KNOW IF THIS IS
A GOOD TIME TO BRING THIS UP,

13:58.327 --> 13:59.828
BUT ME AND SILAS ‐‐

13:59.861 --> 14:01.964
OH, NO. ♪♪ LA LA LA LA LA ♪♪
STOP TALKING.

14:01.997 --> 14:04.032
HE'S LIKE CHRISTIAN GREY
WITHOUT THE MONEY.

14:04.066 --> 14:05.233
IT'S PRETTY FUCKING HOT.

14:05.267 --> 14:06.435
I DON'T KNOW
WHO CHRISTIAN GREY IS.

14:06.468 --> 14:07.436
I DON'T CARE.

14:07.469 --> 14:08.870
SILAS IS A GROWN MAN.

14:08.904 --> 14:10.939
SPEAKING OF GROWN MEN.

14:10.973 --> 14:12.040
HEY.

14:12.074 --> 14:14.076
HANG ON A SEC.

14:14.109 --> 14:16.778
[ LASERS ZAPPING ]

14:16.812 --> 14:18.880
OH, WITH HIS
IDIOT ENTOURAGE.

14:20.882 --> 14:22.084
WONDERFUL.

14:22.117 --> 14:25.754
COULD YOU GIVE ME A ‐‐
JUST GO AWAY FOR A SEC?

14:25.787 --> 14:27.189
[ LASER ZAPS ]

14:27.222 --> 14:28.457
YOU DON'T CALL.

14:28.490 --> 14:29.891
YOU DON'T WRITE.

14:29.925 --> 14:31.159
I WAS IN THE BRIG.

14:31.193 --> 14:33.095
WHAT, THEY DON'T HAVE
MAIL THERE?

14:33.128 --> 14:34.429
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

14:34.463 --> 14:36.465
YOU ONLY CALL ME
WHEN YOU NEED SOMETHING?

14:36.498 --> 14:38.634
SEND YOUR LITTLE HIGH‐HEEL
TOTTERING UNDERLINGS?

14:38.667 --> 14:40.535
I WAS SHOT IN THE HEAD.

14:40.569 --> 14:42.170
OH, CUT THE BULLSHIT.

14:42.204 --> 14:43.705
JUST...

14:43.739 --> 14:47.042
YOU'RE FUCKING
SOMEBODY ELSE, RIGHT?

14:47.075 --> 14:48.577
SHOT IN THE HEAD...

14:48.610 --> 14:50.412
FOR REAL, OKAY?
WHAT?

14:50.445 --> 14:51.880
HOLY SHIT.

14:51.913 --> 14:54.316
JUST SELL TO KIKU, OKAY?

14:54.349 --> 14:56.518
SHE NEEDS WEED.
PLEASE SELL HER YOUR WEED.

14:56.551 --> 14:57.953
WAR'S WINDING DOWN.

14:57.986 --> 15:00.555
MOST OF MY GUYS HAVE SHIPPED
HOME ALREADY, ANYWAY,

15:00.589 --> 15:03.525
AND EVEN IF I COULD GET MY HANDS
ON SUPPLY FOR YOU ‐‐

15:03.558 --> 15:05.460
WHICH I'M NOT SAYING
THAT I CAN ‐‐

15:05.494 --> 15:06.762
BUT EVEN IF I DID,

15:06.795 --> 15:09.298
I WOULD HAVE TO GREASE
SO MANY LOCAL PALMS

15:09.331 --> 15:11.667
THAT YOU AND POSH SPICE
OVER THERE

15:11.700 --> 15:15.304
COULDN'T EVEN BEGIN TO AFFORD
THAT KIND OF OLIVE OIL.

15:15.337 --> 15:17.039
PALM OIL?

15:17.072 --> 15:19.274
I GOT YOU, SEXY DEALER LADY!

15:19.308 --> 15:20.943
[ LASER ZAPPING ]

15:20.976 --> 15:22.778
WHAT THE FUCK
ARE YOU DOING?!
WHAT DID I DO?

15:22.811 --> 15:24.579
SHE'S GOT A BULLET
IN HER HEAD!

15:24.613 --> 15:26.081
[ Distorted ] YOU POINT
A FUCKING LASER GUN AT HER?

15:26.114 --> 15:27.316
FUCKING IDIOT!

15:27.349 --> 15:29.318
I DIDN'T KNOW
SHE TOOK A BULLET, MAN!

15:29.351 --> 15:31.320
HOW WAS I
SUPPOSED TO KNOW THAT?!
WHAT'S HAPPENING?
IS SHE HEMORRHAGING?

15:31.353 --> 15:33.922
YOU OKAY?
HEY, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

15:33.956 --> 15:35.290
I CAN DO MOUTH‐TO‐MOUTH.

15:35.324 --> 15:36.491
I CAN DO IT.

15:36.525 --> 15:39.127
I CAN DO IT ‐‐ WITH MY DICK.
[ LAUGHS ]

15:39.161 --> 15:40.762
WHAT?
Nancy: NO OVERHEAD.

15:40.796 --> 15:42.297
WHAT?

15:42.331 --> 15:44.566
CASH UP FRONT ON TIME.

15:44.600 --> 15:46.668
THAT'S THE...
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

15:46.702 --> 15:49.705
BEST OFFER
YOU'RE GONNA GET.

15:49.738 --> 15:51.740
[ SIGHS ]

15:51.773 --> 15:53.909
ALL RIGHT.

15:53.942 --> 15:55.544
I'LL DEAL WITH YOU.

15:55.577 --> 15:57.980
BUT YOU DON'T GET MY HEART
THIS TIME.

15:58.013 --> 15:59.147
JUST BUSINESS.

15:59.181 --> 16:01.383
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

16:01.416 --> 16:03.318
HEY. YOU OKAY?

16:03.352 --> 16:04.753
EVERYONE KEEPS
ASKING ME THAT.

16:04.786 --> 16:06.321
"ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU OKAY?"

16:06.355 --> 16:07.956
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE PEOPLE ARE CONCERNED.

16:07.990 --> 16:10.559
MAYBE PEOPLE SHOULD MIND
THEIR OWN BUSINESS.

16:10.592 --> 16:13.028
Woman: <i>...HAS TAKEN DAMAGE.</i>
<i>GAME OVER.</i>

16:13.061 --> 16:16.164
<i>PLEASE PROCEED TO EXIT.</i>

16:19.735 --> 16:20.569
I KNEW IT.

16:20.602 --> 16:24.206
I'M...
JUST TAKING INVENTORY!

16:24.239 --> 16:25.841
IN CASE
THERE'S A HURRICANE.

16:25.874 --> 16:28.310
YOU ARE COOKING A GIGANTIC
LOVE FEAST FOR NANCY.

16:28.343 --> 16:30.946
FAMILY LOVE FEAST,
AND I CALLED ELIZABITCH,

16:30.979 --> 16:33.448
AND SHE'S COOL TO COVER
DERBY PRACTICE FOR TONIGHT.

16:33.482 --> 16:34.716
THE GIRLS HATE ELIZABITCH.

16:34.750 --> 16:36.718
SHE ALWAYS STICKING THEM
IN THE PENALTY BOX!

16:36.752 --> 16:38.086
YEAH, IT'S CALLED
"COMPROMISE."

16:38.120 --> 16:39.554
FIRST ZOO AND NOW PAELLA.

16:39.588 --> 16:42.291
I ACTUALLY LIKE YOU, ANDY ‐‐
LIKE, GROWN‐UP LIKE YOU,

16:42.324 --> 16:43.892
LIKE I'M CO‐PARENTING
WITH YOU,

16:43.926 --> 16:46.795
NOT TO MENTION THE FACT THAT
YOUR COCK DOES MAGICAL THINGS.

16:46.828 --> 16:49.831
BUT ALL OF A SUDDEN,
NANCY SPRINGS BACK TO LIFE,

16:49.865 --> 16:52.834
AND SHE'S GOT THE GIMPY LEG
AND HER NEEDY EYES,

16:52.868 --> 16:53.969
AND I DON'T KNOW.

16:54.002 --> 16:56.171
SUDDENLY, YOU'RE COOKING
FOR HER, YOU'RE DISTANT.

16:56.204 --> 16:57.572
YOU HAVEN'T EVEN ONCE
ASKED ME

16:57.606 --> 16:59.541
HOW AM I FEELING ABOUT
THE WHOLE SCOTT SITUATION,

16:59.574 --> 17:01.143
WHICH, BY THE WAY,
IS FREAKING ME OUT.

17:01.176 --> 17:03.512
I NEED TO KNOW THAT YOU ARE
ACTUALLY IN THIS THING WITH ME,

17:03.545 --> 17:05.314
NOT JUST STICKING YOUR TOE
IN THE WATER.

17:05.347 --> 17:06.882
I ONLY HAVE EIGHT TOES.

17:06.915 --> 17:10.385
HEY. COME ON.

17:10.419 --> 17:12.587
COME ON.

17:12.621 --> 17:14.589
MMM.

17:14.623 --> 17:17.559
HEY, WHAT ARE WE DOING?

17:17.593 --> 17:20.162
WE GOT, LIKE,
A GOOD THING GOING ON.

17:20.195 --> 17:23.532
LET'S NOT RUIN IT
BY OVERTHINKING.

17:23.565 --> 17:26.902
THAT WAS THE MOST ARTFULLY
NONCOMMITTAL PHRASE EVER.

17:26.935 --> 17:28.003
NO.
YES.

17:28.036 --> 17:29.805
NO. MAYBE.

17:29.838 --> 17:31.006
I don't know.

17:31.039 --> 17:32.874
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

17:32.908 --> 17:34.242
YOU HAVE COMPANY.

17:34.276 --> 17:36.411
Wade: THAT'S HIM.

17:36.445 --> 17:39.081
SIR, DID YOU GRAFFITI
THIS DOG?

17:39.114 --> 17:40.582
HMM.

17:40.616 --> 17:42.884
SHE MUST HAVE TAKEN A NAP
ON ONE OF MY DAY‐GLO PAINTINGS,

17:42.918 --> 17:44.620
WHERE I WROTE
THOSE LETTERS BACKWARDS.

17:44.653 --> 17:46.021
IT'S VERY POST‐MODERN.

17:46.054 --> 17:47.055
LIAR.

17:47.089 --> 17:48.657
GILDA ONLY NAPS ON PILLOWS.

17:48.690 --> 17:50.158
WHAT KIND OF NAME
IS GILDA?

17:50.192 --> 17:51.293
MY GRANDMOTHER'S NAME.

17:51.326 --> 17:52.628
OH.

17:52.661 --> 17:54.730
AND DOES YOUR GRANDMOTHER
ALSO SHIT AND RUN?

17:54.763 --> 17:55.697
SHE'S DEAD.

17:55.731 --> 17:57.532
AND SHE WAS
A STATE SENATOR!

17:57.566 --> 17:59.701
JOHN, HELP ME OUT HERE,
PLEASE.

17:59.735 --> 18:01.670
MM, TECHNICALLY,
I CAN'T WRITE HIM UP

18:01.703 --> 18:03.972
FOR SPRAY‐PAINTING A DOG.

18:04.006 --> 18:07.175
QUOTE, "IT IS ILLEGAL TO PAINT
A COW OR A SHORT‐HAIRED GOAT,"

18:07.209 --> 18:08.477
OLD SANDWICH ORDINANCE 81‐3.

18:08.510 --> 18:10.178
IT DOESN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT DOGS.

18:10.212 --> 18:13.582
NOW, WHAT ABOUT TRESPASSING ON
SOMEONE'S YARD AND MAKING CACA?

18:13.615 --> 18:15.684
OH, THAT'S A $200 FINE.

18:15.717 --> 18:18.020
HE CAN'T PROVE SHIT
ABOUT SHIT!

18:18.053 --> 18:19.288
WELL, GOT TO GO.

18:19.321 --> 18:21.323
FEEL A BOWEL MOVEMENT
COMING ON MYSELF.

18:21.356 --> 18:22.557
YOU HAVE A NICE DAY, NOW.

18:22.591 --> 18:25.160
OH, FUCK YOU, WILSON!

18:25.193 --> 18:27.095
FUCK YOU!

18:27.129 --> 18:28.397
[ DOG BARKS ]

18:31.500 --> 18:34.169
[ SNIFFS ]
DO YOU USE BAT GUANO?

18:34.202 --> 18:36.505
NO.
NO, SHOULD I?

18:36.538 --> 18:39.174
OH, YEAH. IT HELPS WITH
THE ROOT DEVELOPMENT.

18:39.207 --> 18:41.710
I USE PERUVIAN, BUT YOU CAN USE
JAMAICAN OR INDONESIAN.

18:41.743 --> 18:43.712
MIKE, THE SPITTER ‐‐
HE SELLS BOTH.
COOL.

18:43.745 --> 18:47.182
YEAH, I'VE HEARD OF PEOPLE
MAKING, UH, NUTRIENT TEA

18:47.215 --> 18:49.384
WITH, LIKE,
WORM CASTINGS AND ‐‐

18:49.418 --> 18:51.620
HEY. CAN YOU LOCK UP
THE GROW HOUSE TONIGHT?

18:51.653 --> 18:52.721
WHY?

18:52.754 --> 18:55.290
I'M HAVING SOMEONE OVER ‐‐
A GIRL.

18:55.324 --> 18:57.125
ARE YOU HAVING A PLAY DATE?

18:57.159 --> 18:58.894
HEY, I'M R. J.

19:00.062 --> 19:02.097
I NEED TO BORROW THIS.

19:02.130 --> 19:06.501
I'M SETTING UP SURVEILLANCE
TO CATCH SOMEONE NAMED GILDA.

19:09.204 --> 19:11.506
SO, IS YOUR BROTHER
IN SECURITY?

19:11.540 --> 19:15.911
NO. HE'S A...CADET.

19:15.944 --> 19:17.479
ROTC?

19:19.081 --> 19:20.515
POLICE ACADEMY.

19:20.549 --> 19:23.785
BUT IN THE CITY, THOUGH,
NOT IN CONNECTICUT.

19:23.819 --> 19:25.454
DUDE, THAT IS
SERIOUSLY FUCKED UP!

19:25.487 --> 19:27.255
NO. IT'S...

19:27.289 --> 19:29.958
IT'S COOL.
I MEAN, WE MAKE IT WORK.

19:29.992 --> 19:31.994
YEAH, FOR NOW,
BUT WAIT TILL HE HAS A BADGE

19:32.027 --> 19:34.429
AND FRIENDS IN EVERY DEPARTMENT
IN NEW YORK CITY.

19:34.463 --> 19:36.832
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT KIND
OF POWER DOES TO SOMEBODY?

19:36.865 --> 19:39.368
DUDE, IF MY BROTHER WAS BECOMING
A COP, I'D BE TERRIFIED.

19:39.401 --> 19:40.669
I'D CHANGE MY NAME
TO VLADIMIR.

19:40.702 --> 19:42.671
BUT, HEY, THAT'S JUST ME,

19:42.704 --> 19:46.408
YOU KNOW,
AND MY BROTHER'S AN ASSHOLE.

19:46.441 --> 19:48.543
[ CHUCKLES ]

19:53.844 --> 19:55.479
I SET UP FOUR
NIGHT‐VISION CAMERAS ‐‐

19:55.513 --> 19:57.548
TWO OVER THE GARAGE
AND TWO IN THE FRONT.

19:57.581 --> 19:58.616
PLUS MOTION DETECTORS.

19:58.649 --> 20:00.017
YOU OWE ME 300 BUCKS.

20:00.050 --> 20:01.652
Nancy: WHERE'S STEVIE?

20:01.685 --> 20:03.220
Andy: OH, NANCE.

20:03.254 --> 20:04.789
HEY, DECIDED TO COOK
AFTER ALL,

20:04.822 --> 20:06.657
JUST A FEW COURSES ‐‐
COMPROMISE, RIGHT?

20:06.690 --> 20:10.795
MOM, THIS IS ANGELA.
ANGELA, NANCY.

20:10.828 --> 20:12.897
IT'S SO NEAT TO MEET YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:12.930 --> 20:15.499
WHAT A NEAT SURPRISE.

20:15.533 --> 20:16.901
I INVITED HER TO DINNER.

20:20.438 --> 20:22.339
UM, WHERE'S STEVIE?

20:22.373 --> 20:24.608
IN [SIGHS]

20:28.412 --> 20:31.348
I TOLD HER NOT TO.

20:32.716 --> 20:34.919
POOR GUY.

20:34.952 --> 20:37.288
HE LOVED
THE KOMODO DRAGON EXHIBIT,

20:37.321 --> 20:40.057
BUT I THINK HE MIGHT BE
ALLERGIC TO LIONS.

20:40.091 --> 20:42.760
HIS NOSE STARTED TO RUN.

20:42.793 --> 20:44.528
I GAVE HIM DIMETAPP.

20:44.562 --> 20:47.064
KNOCKED HIM RIGHT OUT.

20:47.098 --> 20:49.767
Announcer:
<i>OH! WHAT A SHOT!</i>

20:49.800 --> 20:50.768
[ <i>CHEERS AND APPLAUSE</i>]

20:50.801 --> 20:53.938
SO, YOU'RE ALSO A COP?

20:53.971 --> 20:57.274
YEP ‐‐ THIRD‐GENERATION.

20:57.308 --> 20:58.542
IT'S FUNNY.

20:58.576 --> 21:01.345
IN GYM CLASS GROWING UP,
SHANE COULDN'T DO A PULL‐UP.

21:01.378 --> 21:05.082
HAD TO DO THAT 30‐SECOND
CHIN HANG WITH THE GIRLS.

21:05.116 --> 21:07.418
Shane: YEAH, WELL,
SILAS IS UNEMPLOYED.

21:07.451 --> 21:08.919
SELF‐EMPLOYED.

21:08.953 --> 21:10.321
HE WORKED
AS A BELLHOP ONCE.

21:10.354 --> 21:13.657
WHY WERE WE WORKING
AT A HOTEL?

21:13.691 --> 21:15.926
ON THE RUN BECAUSE OF...

21:15.960 --> 21:17.461
THAT MEXICUNT, RIGHT?

21:18.429 --> 21:19.797
THE ONE SHANE HIT?

21:19.830 --> 21:21.632
WHAT, NO HIT?
NO HITTING?

21:21.665 --> 21:23.634
CUNT? BAD WORD?

21:23.667 --> 21:24.635
[ GLASS CLINKS ]

21:24.668 --> 21:26.303
I'D LIKE TO WELCOME EVERYONE

21:26.337 --> 21:31.075
TO THE BOTWIN‐PRICE‐GRAY
FAMILY DINNER ‐‐ TAKE 2,

21:31.108 --> 21:32.943
CONTINUING [CHUCKLES]

21:32.977 --> 21:36.547
WHERE WE LEFT OFF BEFORE
WE WERE SO RUDELY INTERRUPTED

21:36.580 --> 21:38.082
BY A .22‐CALIBER BULLET.

21:38.115 --> 21:42.086
ANGELA, R. J., WELCOME.

21:42.119 --> 21:45.389
I HAVEN'T REALLY SPOKEN
TO EITHER OF YOU YET,

21:45.423 --> 21:46.791
BUT I'M ‐‐ I'M SO GLAD

21:46.824 --> 21:49.927
MY SONS FELT COMFORTABLE
BRINGING YOU HERE ‐‐

21:49.960 --> 21:53.497
WILL FEEL COMFORTABLE
BRINGING PEOPLE HERE.

21:53.531 --> 21:56.801
AS LIFE GOES ON...

21:56.834 --> 21:59.570
GETS MORE COMPLICATED,

21:59.603 --> 22:01.539
ROADS DIVERGE,

22:01.572 --> 22:04.508
I LOVE YOU BOTH SO MUCH ‐‐

22:04.542 --> 22:06.110
ALL THREE OF YOU, ACTUALLY,

22:06.143 --> 22:09.747
BECAUSE THERE WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
THREE OF MY SONS AT THIS TABLE,

22:09.780 --> 22:12.116
BUT JILL PUT JUDAH TO BED.

22:12.149 --> 22:14.251
SO...

22:14.285 --> 22:16.487
WHAT?

22:18.656 --> 22:20.891
YOU MEAN STEVIE?

22:20.925 --> 22:21.992
WHAT DID I SAY?

22:22.026 --> 22:23.260
YOU SAID, "JUDAH."

22:23.294 --> 22:24.795
NO, I DIDN'T.

22:24.829 --> 22:26.464
YEAH. [ SNIFFS ]

22:31.402 --> 22:33.370
NO.

22:40.911 --> 22:43.080
NANCE? PANTS.

22:43.114 --> 22:44.682
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HER?

22:44.715 --> 22:46.050
I DON'T KNOW!
HOW WOULD I KNOW?!

22:46.083 --> 22:48.452
I TOLD HER NOT TO GO, DIDN'T I?
DIDN'T I?

22:48.486 --> 22:50.888
YOU'RE BOTH SO
COMPLETELY IRRESPONSIBLE.

22:50.921 --> 22:53.124
PERFECT. GO FOR IT.
LET IT ALL OUT ‐‐ AGAIN.

22:53.157 --> 22:54.859
ANDY, IT'S CALLED
COMMUNICATION.

22:54.892 --> 22:56.494
IT'S CALLED DIMETAPP.

22:56.527 --> 22:58.796
IT'S CALLED DRUGGING A CHILD
TO MASK YOUR OWN INSECURITIES.

22:58.829 --> 23:00.030
I'M GONNA GO PICK UP THE GIRLS
FROM PRACTICE.

23:00.064 --> 23:01.165
DO NOT FOLLOW ME.

23:01.198 --> 23:03.667
WE'RE DONE, ANDY!
[ CHAIR SCRAPES ]

23:03.701 --> 23:05.803
UH, MRS. BOTWIN,
ARE YOU OKAY?

23:05.836 --> 23:07.805
HUH? UH‐HUH.

23:07.838 --> 23:09.507
Whimsy: WADE, NO!
Wade: EAT SHIT, WILSON!

23:09.540 --> 23:10.741
OH!

23:10.775 --> 23:11.809
OH, WHAT THE FUCK?!

23:11.842 --> 23:14.278
[ SPITTING ]

23:14.311 --> 23:15.780
OHH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:15.813 --> 23:18.349
WHAT?
I DIDN'T THROW SHIT AT YOU.

23:18.382 --> 23:19.483
OH, NARC.

23:19.517 --> 23:21.819
TECHNICALLY, "NARC" REFERS
TO THE NARCOTICS UNIT.

23:21.852 --> 23:23.254
FINE, YOU WANT TO BE A COP?

23:23.287 --> 23:25.589
YOU WANT TO GET HIGH
ON YOUR OWN POWER? ENJOY.

23:25.623 --> 23:27.425
WHAT?
SILAS, WAIT.

23:29.293 --> 23:31.395
[ SNIFFS ]

23:31.429 --> 23:33.898
YEAH, DEFINITELY SHIT.

23:33.931 --> 23:36.467
[ SIGHS ]

23:36.500 --> 23:38.569
AMBIEN?

23:49.380 --> 23:51.182
[ SIGHS ]

23:53.584 --> 23:57.888
I COLLAPSED AT LASER TAG.

23:59.457 --> 24:02.193
THERE WERE ALL THESE...
STROBE LIGHTS.

24:02.226 --> 24:05.596
WELL, YOU'RE ALLOWED TO SHOW
A LITTLE VULNERABILITY, I THINK.

24:05.629 --> 24:09.066
AND...

24:11.068 --> 24:13.704
[ Voice breaking ]
...I FORGOT HIS NAME.

24:13.737 --> 24:15.439
OH, YOU DID.

24:15.473 --> 24:20.111
BUT YOUR BRAIN IS STILL
REORGANIZING ITSELF.

24:20.144 --> 24:21.946
GREAT.

24:21.979 --> 24:25.683
SO STEVIE WILL HAVE
A ZOMBIE FOR A MOTHER.

24:25.716 --> 24:27.418
THERE. YOU GOT IT RIGHT ‐‐
STEVIE.

24:27.451 --> 24:28.619
[ LAUGHS ]

24:28.652 --> 24:30.020
THAT WAS MEAN
WHAT JILL DID.

24:30.054 --> 24:33.023
I THINK SHE WAS LASHING OUT
AT ME, NOT YOU ‐‐

24:33.057 --> 24:35.926
EVEN THOUGH I CHOSE HER
THIS MORNING.

24:35.960 --> 24:38.429
AND THEN I CHOSE YOU,
THE FAMILY.

24:38.462 --> 24:43.033
WHY DOES COMMITMENT
HAVE TO BE EXCLUSIVE, HUH?

24:43.067 --> 24:46.403
ANYWAY, I'LL BE SLEEPING ON
THE WINDOW BENCH TONIGHT, SO...

24:46.437 --> 24:48.539
[ CHUCKLES, SNIFFLES ]

24:48.572 --> 24:51.308
...IF YOU WANT TO TALK...

24:53.844 --> 24:55.446
[ SNIFFLES ]

24:58.549 --> 24:59.784
[ WHIMPERS ]

24:59.817 --> 25:01.585
[ SNIFFLING ]

25:05.222 --> 25:07.491
Stevie: MOMMY?
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:07.525 --> 25:10.227
YES, SWEETIE?

25:11.962 --> 25:13.864
I CAN'T SLEEP.

25:13.898 --> 25:16.867
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
AWW.

25:16.901 --> 25:18.803
YOU KNOW WHAT?

25:18.836 --> 25:20.938
ME NEITHER.

25:22.406 --> 25:24.175
[ SMOOCHING ]

25:27.044 --> 25:31.515
Hey, can you keep
a secret?

25:31.549 --> 25:35.953
ALL RIGHT. 1, 2, 3.

25:35.986 --> 25:38.189
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

25:38.222 --> 25:40.157
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:40.191 --> 25:43.194
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

26:07.351 --> 26:11.689
♪♪ I SHOULD TRY TO BE GOOD ♪♪

26:11.722 --> 26:15.259
♪♪ FOREVER AND EVER ♪♪

26:15.292 --> 26:16.527
♪♪ AMEN ♪♪

26:16.560 --> 26:20.197
♪♪ SO I'LL TOUCH WOOD ♪♪

26:20.231 --> 26:24.735
♪♪ AND HOPE I DON'T GET
CAUGHT AGAIN ♪♪

26:24.769 --> 26:27.938
♪♪ WITHOUT MY LINES ♪♪
[ SIGHS ]

26:27.972 --> 26:31.242
♪♪ AND OFF THE MARK ♪♪

26:31.275 --> 26:34.779
♪♪ LOOKING FOR SIGNS ♪♪

26:34.812 --> 26:38.115
♪♪ I CAN'T SEE HERE IN THE DARK ♪♪

26:38.149 --> 26:41.051
YOU ARE MINE, GILDA,
